ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: NURS913 is a great course with rich class discussion centered around self-management of disease. I would recommend this course to other students.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: This course was helpful in that self-management is applicable to a wide variety of disciplines in health care. However, I do not feel this class was the most helpful in terms of my own research. It was very interesting and I feel I learned a lot.
Deepened my understanding of scholarly work in the profession significantly. Did not contribute to my dissertation/research.

It was at times difficult to apply the course content to my own dissertation work, as I am not focusing on management of chronic illnesses. It was important content to be aware of and learn about, but I think a half-semester would have been sufficient for my own needs.
